        "subject": "LU-19796 kfilnd: fix sg_table free after orig_nents overwrite",
        "message": "LU-19796 kfilnd: fix sg_table free after orig_nents overwrite\n\nThe kfilnd transaction code was overwriting sg_table.orig_nents\nwith the actual number of populated segments to work around\ndma_[un]map_sgtable() requirements. However, orig_nents must\nremain the original allocation size so sg_free_table() can\ndetermine whether to dismantle a chained multi-page table or\njust issue kfree().\n\nThis caused kernel warnings in free_nonslab_page() when freeing\ntransactions with scatter-gather tables:\n\n  WARNING: CPU: 1 PID: 806 at mm/slub.c:3591 free_nonslab_page+0x70/0x90\n  Call Trace:\n    kfree+0x20e/0x250\n    __sg_free_table+0x5f/0x80\n    kfilnd_tn_free+0x23a/0x3a0 [kkfilnd]\n\nThe fix introduces tn_sgt_alloc_nents to save the original\nallocation size and kfilnd_tn_sgt_free() to restore orig_nents\nbefore calling sg_free_table(). This preserves the allocation\nmetadata needed for proper cleanup while still allowing the\ndma mapping functions to work with only the populated segments.\n\nAdditional changes:\n- Move tn_num_iovec outside HAVE_KFI_SGL ifdef since it's only\n  used in the non-SGL code path\n- Update debug messages to use tn_sgt.nents instead of the\n  removed tn_num_iovec assignment\n- Add alloc_nents to debug output for better diagnostics\n\nFixes: 86775f2d6f (\"LUS-10076 kfilnd: GDS support for kfilnd\")\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-13118\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ib9eac555f1a665991ef1baf45530905de732d5ee\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63434\nReviewed-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Alexey Lyashkov <alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
